# AIMED Self-Declaration Rules

All AI-generated or AI-modified code in this project must include an AIMED/1 transparency declaration per the aiMed open standard (https://github.com/krdr-mft/aimed).

## Required Behavior

1. When you create a new file, add `// AIMED/1 <scores> | tool=cursor` as the first comment.
2. When you generate a function or class, add the declaration to its docblock.
3. When composing a commit message, add the declaration as the last line.

## Scoring

Rate your involvement per area on a 0-5 scale:
- D (Drafting): How much of the code you wrote. D:5 = you wrote it all.
- E (Editing): How much you refactored or improved. E:4 = major refactor.
- S (Strategy): How much you decided the approach. S:0 = human told you exactly what to do.
- V (Validation): How much you reviewed or tested. V:3 = you checked it meaningfully.

Only include areas where you contributed. When uncertain, score higher.

## Examples

```typescript
// AIMED/1 D:5 E:3 V:2 | tool=cursor

export class AuthService {
    // ...
}
```

```python
def process_payment(order_id: str) -> PaymentResult:
    """Process payment for the given order.
    
    AIMED/1 S:2 D:5 E:3 | tool=cursor
    """
    ...
```
